  "explanation": "IBM App Connect Enterprise is collected by subscribing to IBM MQ pub/sub topics over MQI (via `pymqi`). The check requires `mq_server`, `mq_port`, `channel`, and `queue_manager`, none of which are discoverable on the wire: `channel` and `queue_manager` are administrator-defined identifiers configured inside the MQ broker, and standard production deployments authenticate the channel with `mq_user`/`mq_password` (and frequently TLS using a `.kdb` key repository plus a cipher spec). The Agent must also be running on a host with the IBM MQ client libraries installed. No combination of host+port probes yields the channel/QM names or credentials.",
